#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""tide-mirror: render a tide retrospective .tex into a therisensea HTML mirror.

Step 4 of the Tide loop calls for a 1-to-1 HTML mirror of the LaTeX
retrospective on therisensea.org (see ../tide/SKILL.md). This script
automates that step: it reads <repo>/retrospectives/<slug>.tex, emits
the HTML page in the therisensea clone's tides/<slug>/index.html, and
splices the entry into the chronological home index.

The conventions match the previously-mirrored retrospectives on
therisensea/main (see commits 938201b and f5992a0):

  - <h1>Tide retrospective: <em>title</em></h1> if the source title is
    \\emph-wrapped, otherwise <h1>Tide retrospective: title</h1>.
  - Header back-link, no nav.
  - Kicker line "<YYYY-MM-DD> · <repo-slug>".
  - Abstract rendered as plain paragraphs.
  - \\section{X} -> <h2>X</h2>; \\paragraph{X} -> <h4>X.</h4>.
  - \\gptbox / \\userbox / \\claudebox -> <blockquote> with a <strong> tag.
  - Theorem-like \\begin{quote}\\itshape ... \\end{quote} -> <blockquote><em>...</em></blockquote>.
  - Footnotes dropped.
  - Display math \\[...\\] normalised to $$...$$ (KaTeX handles both).

Usage.

  tide-mirror render <repo> <slug>
      Render a single retrospective. <repo> is the seabed Lean repo
      under sri/lean/ (e.g. modes-lean); <slug> is the .tex basename
      with or without the .tex extension. Writes
      <therisensea>/tides/<slug>/index.html.

  tide-mirror close <repo> <slug>
      Render + splice into the home index. Use this at the end of a
      Tide's Step 4 — it produces the page and updates the chronological
      list in one shot.

  tide-mirror reindex
      Regenerate <therisensea>/index.html from every tides/*/index.html
      directory. Use after manual edits, deletions, or to backfill.

  tide-mirror sync
      For every retrospective .tex under sri/lean/*/retrospectives/,
      ensure tides/<slug>/index.html exists in the therisensea clone.
      Skips entries already present. Then reindex. Useful for backfill.

Path discovery.

  SRI root: the directory containing this script, walking upward to
            find lean/, papers/, projects/. Override with SRI_ROOT.
  therisensea clone: the THERISENSEA_DIR env var, or a sibling of the
            SRI root's parent named "therisensea", or fall back to
            ~/timaeus/therisensea. Override with --therisensea.

Slug conventions.

  Mobius-surface retrospectives use the dir slug without "-tide-"
  (matching 2026-05-19-mobius-surface-hasfderiv, hand-mirrored on
  origin/main). All other tides keep the "-tide-" segment.
"""

